Implemented the Flask recruiting app with:

- SQLite-backed users, jobs, and applications
- Employer/applicant roles and ownership checks
- bcrypt password hashing
- CSRF protection on POST routes
- Secure session cookie settings and security headers
- Parameterized SQLite queries throughout
- Hardened resume uploads with size limits, content inspection, random filenames, and protected download access
- Templates, stylesheet, `requirements.txt`, and README run instructions for port `5070`

Files created include [app.py](C:/Users/Darko/AppData/Local/Temp/csj_gen_tz_pvpm9/app.py), [requirements.txt](C:/Users/Darko/AppData/Local/Temp/csj_gen_tz_pvpm9/requirements.txt), [README.md](C:/Users/Darko/AppData/Local/Temp/csj_gen_tz_pvpm9/README.md), templates, and [static/styles.css](C:/Users/Darko/AppData/Local/Temp/csj_gen_tz_pvpm9/static/styles.css).

